text: Eudonia albilinea is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Sasaki in 1998. It is found in Taiwan., 2012: One new species of the genus Eudonia Billberg (Lepidoptera: Crambidae: Scopariinae) from China. Entomotaxonomia 34 (2): 267-269. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1998 Category:Scopariinae
